snippet.textDisplay: about step 3 in colorfix: i've used colorfix for years and step 3 is one hell of a mess, i don't know why it's in the box. i have lightened my hair from black to a medium red color with colorfix, but as soon as i put step 3 on (per the instructions), it would turn all my hair back to black immediately. i tried it a couple of other times thinking i did something wrong, but step 3 is simply fucked UP and useless. i've come across a lot of videos where people toss step 3 into the trash because they know it'll reverse the lightening they're about to do.

snippet.textDisplay:
I'm not sure if this is technically correct and sorry if my english's bad but I try
My hairdresser told me that this 'dont bleech your hair more than once a day' is not because of the damage it does, its simply not working properly. The pigments are not centered in the hair, they are flat in some kind of way and are lying in different directions kind of...so if you bleech your hair you only hit the pigments that are lined up in the same direction that time and not the pigments lying differently. As the hair grows and the pigments move, the pigments position changes and another round of bleech will get them. Dont quote me on that but I think that sounds quiet possible xD
